
<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- This line tells the browser this is an HTML5 document -->
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <!-- The <head> holds information ABOUT the page (not shown directly on the page) -->
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My First Web Page</title>

    <!-- Link to the external CSS file for styling -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <!-- The <body> holds everything that actually appears on the page -->
    <div class="card">
        <h1>Welcome!</h1>
        <p>This is my very first web page, built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
        <p>It shows the basic structure every HTML document follows: a <code>head</code> section for page info, and a <code>body</code> section for visible content.</p>

        <button id="greetBtn">Click me!</button>
        <p id="greetMessage"></p>

        <span class="tag">Made with HTML, CSS &amp; JS</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Link to the external JavaScript file for behavior -->
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
